{"lemma":"آكِل","slug":"آكِل","root":"#.ك.ل","root_slug":"_-ك-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ك-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"آكِل","root":"أكل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n998","n999","n1000","n1001"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A2%D9%83%D9%90%D9%84"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to eat together with another, share in another's meal","examples":[{"text":"وَأَنَا كَيْفَ أُؤَاكِلُ أَقْوَامًا يَصْنَعُونَ هٰذَا الصَّنِيعَ ثُمَّ يَحْتَجُّونَ لَهُ بِمِثْلِ هَذِهِ الْحُجَجِ؟","english":"How can I eat with folk who do such as they do, and, in support of it, argue with such arguments as these?”"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to give something to eat, to feed","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to invite to eat","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sow discord","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bring forth fruit","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bring one in another's power","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of أَكَلَ (ʔakala)","tags":["active","form-of","obsolete","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"-vore","tags":["obsolete"],"examples":[{"text":"اَلْحَيَوَانَاتُ آكِلَةُ اللُّحُومِ","english":"carnivore animals"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"who eats more","tags":["obsolete","rare"],"examples":[{"text":"فَقَالَ لَهُ صَاحِبُهُ: لَوْلَا أَعْلَمُ أَنَّكَ آكَلُ مِنِّي لَأَدْخَلْتُ لَكَ هٰذَا الْكَلَامَ فِي بَابِ النَّصِيحَةِ.","english":"And his friend said to him: If I were not to know that you are more esurient than I am, I would have commenced my advice with this introductory word."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"See the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n998","headword_ar":"اُكْلٌ","root":"Akl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukulN","text_ar":"اُكُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n999","headword_ar":"اَكَلٌ","root":"Akl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akila","text_ar":"اَكِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY A^asonaAnihi A^akalN","text_ar":"فِى اَسْنَانِهِ اَكَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In his teeth is a rubbing together and wasting away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of age. (S, TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukulN","text_ar":"اُكُلٌ"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n1000","headword_ar":"اَكِلٌ","root":"Akl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akila","text_ar":"اَكِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN A^akilapN","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ اَكِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-camel experiencing an itching and annoyance in her belly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the growth of the hair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the growth of the fur,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of her fœtus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAakilu","text_ar":"الاَكِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put, in the CK, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA=kilu","text_ar":"الا=كِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a sense explained below.]"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n1001","headword_ar":"اُكُلٌ","root":"Akl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukolN","text_ar":"اُكْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K, &c.;) the latter a contraction of the former; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is eaten;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukolapN","text_ar":"اُكْلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akolapN","text_ar":"اَكْلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^okalapN","text_ar":"مَاْكَلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^okulapN","text_ar":"مَاْكُلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^okuwlN","text_ar":"مَاْكُولٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lh, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any eatable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that is eaten;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akaAlN","text_ar":"اَكَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the same, an eatable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) You say of one who is dead,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinoqaTaEa A^ukuluhu","text_ar":"اِنْقَطَعَ اُكُلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His food has become cut off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the TA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akoluhu","text_ar":"اَكْلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1]. (S.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA *uqotu A^akaAl~aA","text_ar":"مَا ذُقْتُ اَكَالَّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have not tasted food."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fruit"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K [in the latter of which, in some copies,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~amoru","text_ar":"التَّمْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~amaru","text_ar":"الثَّمَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", erroneously, as is said in the TA]) of palmtrees and other trees [&c.]. (S.) So in the Kur [xiii. 35],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukuluhaA daAy^imN","text_ar":"اُكُلُهَا دَايِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Its fruit"},{"kind":"text","text":"shall be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perpetual"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) meaning that the fruits thereof shall be not as those of the present world, which come to one at one time and not at another. (TA.) [Pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=kaAlN","text_ar":"ا=كَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; occurring in the M and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Atw","text_ar":"اتو"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Means of subsistence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worldly good fortune,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and ample means of subsistence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN *uw A^ukulK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ ذُو اُكُلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is possessed of worldly good fortune, and ample means of subsistence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZiymu AlA^ukuli","text_ar":"عَظِيمُ الاُكُلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessed of [great] good fortune;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a [great and] good share of the means of subsistence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thickness, substantialness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"closeness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compactness of texture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a garment, or piece of cloth; (S, K, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (K.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN *uw A^ukulK","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ ذُو اُكُلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth, having thickness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiroTaAsN *uw A^ukulK","text_ar":"قِرْطَاسٌ ذُو اُكُلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"paper having thickness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (S, TA.) ―         -b5-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Intelligence; judgment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Nasr, S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firmness of intellect."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN *uw A^ukulK","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ ذُو اُكُلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man possessing intelligence and judgment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Nasr, S, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Lh","TA","Msb","K","S"]}]}}